    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nI’d like to propose adding minimal built-in indentation guides to Neovim.\n\nIndentation guides are one of the most commonly installed visual enhancements in the Neovim ecosystem. Many users install plugins such as indent-blankline.nvim or mini.indentscope almost immediately after setting up Neovim.\n\nRecent Neovim releases have also moved toward including more sensible built-in functionality and defaults, such as:\n\n- built-in commenting support (gcc, etc.)\n- bundled themes like retrobox and catppuccin\n- built-in plugins/features that previously required external plugins\n\nA minimal indentation guide feature seems aligned with that direction.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe idea would not be to replace advanced indentation plugins, but simply to provide a lightweight built-in implementation for the common case.\n\nSomething minimal could already be very useful, for example:\n\n- showing vertical indentation guides\n- a simple enable/disable option\n- basic highlight support\n\nAdvanced features could remain in external plugins, while Neovim provides a small and fast default implementation for users who only need basic indentation visualization.",
